HEADWORD: Centinody
<hw>Cen*tin"o*dy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>centum</ets> a hundred + <ets>nodus</ets> knot: cf. F.
<ets>centinode</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A weed with a stem
of many joints (<spn>Illecebrum verticillatum</spn>); also, the
<spn>Polygonum aviculare</spn> or knotgrass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

